Don’t let them meet.

66
00:07:37,702 --> 00:07:39,120
Hello, Luangpor.

67
00:07:39,291 --> 00:07:40,194
Tharn.

68
00:07:40,342 --> 00:07:42,320
I need your advice on something.

69
00:07:42,700 --> 00:07:43,508
Okay.

70
00:07:47,725 --> 00:07:48,674
Wake up, Tharn.

71
00:07:48,697 --> 00:07:51,348
It wasn’t just your voice that I heard.

72
00:07:52,605 --> 00:07:54,788
I also heard someone else’s voice.

73
00:07:55,177 --> 00:07:57,611
That person was screaming in pain.

74
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:02,331
The voice sounded so familiar.

75
00:08:03,120 --> 00:08:11,820
Bounded by a chain of karma and the ego that knows no end,
he is coming back to reclaim what once belonged to him.

76
00:08:13,554 --> 00:08:15,234
What do you mean by that?

77
00:08:16,628 --> 00:08:23,062
Tharn, you and Phaya must be more careful during these days.

78
00:08:23,470 --> 00:08:30,651
Always be mindful. The danger can occur in any moment.

79
00:08:31,497 --> 00:08:33,108
What danger, Luangpor?

80
00:08:34,068 --> 00:08:38,660
You both will face a serious problem.

81
00:08:39,245 --> 00:08:41,097
Stay mindful and use your wisdom.

82
00:08:41,920 --> 00:08:48,860
Remember, your good deeds and merits will always protect you.

83
00:08:49,417 --> 00:08:54,034
Also, try to stay away from the river.

84
00:08:54,342 --> 00:08:56,000
Because it’s where he lives.

85
00:08:58,537 --> 00:08:59,794
Yes, Luangpor.

86
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:25,211
[Phaya: I already put your clothes in a washer.]

87
00:09:25,931 --> 00:09:27,920
[Phaya: You can wear my clothes to work today.]

88
00:09:28,285 --> 00:09:31,268
[Phaya: Hurry up and get dressed then come down for breakfast.]

89
00:10:12,217 --> 00:10:13,440
Hey.

90
00:10:16,697 --> 00:10:19,700
Does it fit? I think it’s a little too big.

91
00:10:21,142 --> 00:10:22,480
It’s okay.

92
00:10:23,580 --> 00:10:28,034
I made you a sandwich. Try it.

93
00:10:30,502 --> 00:10:34,297
Go on. I want to know if you like it or not.

94
00:10:40,068 --> 00:10:42,628
Where is your Grandma?

95
00:10:43,280 --> 00:10:45,314
I want to say goodbye to her before we go to work.

96
00:10:46,091 --> 00:10:50,342
My sister took her to see a friend.

97
00:10:52,948 --> 00:10:57,485
Do you want sugar?

98
00:10:59,337 --> 00:11:00,342
I’ll have two of that.

99
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:01,942
Two?

100
00:11:09,417 --> 00:11:10,331
Hmm

101
00:11:18,788 --> 00:11:20,262
Why did you kiss me?

102
00:11:20,260 --> 00:11:22,971
Well, you said you wanted two of that.

103
00:11:23,560 --> 00:11:27,302
So, I just gave you my sweetest kisses. Do you want more?

104
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:30,525
Quit it. I meant the sugar.

105
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:33,531
If you keep eating like that, you’ll get diabetes soon.

106
00:11:33,700 --> 00:11:36,514
Better have my sweet kiss instead. It’s good for your health.

107
00:11:38,914 --> 00:11:41,622
Whatever, I don’t want it anymore.

108
00:11:41,782 --> 00:11:42,537
Aww

109
00:11:55,748 --> 00:11:59,542
By the way, I just talked to the Abbot.

110
00:12:00,331 --> 00:12:02,765
I told him about your bad dream.

111
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:05,440
He asked me to warn you...

112
00:12:05,474 --> 00:12:07,508
to try to stay away from the river.

113
00:12:09,970 --> 00:12:13,782
But can I stay close to you then?

114
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:17,885
Quit fooling around. I’m being serious.

115
00:12:20,045 --> 00:12:24,182
It might have something to do with why you had a bad dream last night.

116
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:42,994
But it’s just a dream after all. Don’t worry too much.

117
00:12:47,451 --> 00:12:52,525
Or maybe, it might be because I decided to be with you.

118
00:12:54,114 --> 00:12:57,497
Hey, stop that. It’s totally unrelated.

119
00:12:57,970 --> 00:13:01,131
I already told you, haven’t I? That I’ll always be by your side.

120
00:13:01,771 --> 00:13:05,485
Well, if you’re that worried,

121
00:13:05,980 --> 00:13:09,074
why don’t you move in with me  so that we can be together all the time?

122
00:13:09,668 --> 00:13:10,285
Wanna do that?

123
00:13:10,308 --> 00:13:10,990
No.

124
00:13:12,308 --> 00:13:13,222
I’ll let you say it again.

125
00:13:16,102 --> 00:13:16,822
No.

126
00:13:20,130 --> 00:13:22,891
But my bed is so soft. You had already tried it last night.

127
00:13:24,822 --> 00:13:26,640
Ouch.

128
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:30,834
What are you doing?

129
00:13:35,394 --> 00:13:36,537
It’s a mess now.

130
00:13:55,245 --> 00:13:57,565
Hurry up and finish your breakfast so that we can go to work.

131
00:13:58,377 --> 00:13:59,268
I know that.

132
00:13:59,291 --> 00:14:00,537
Stop smiling like a fool.

133
00:14:03,188 --> 00:14:04,022
Tharn!

134
00:14:04,850 --> 00:14:06,217
Tharn! Where are you?

135
