You can’t beat me.

147
00:15:19,796 --> 00:15:22,576
If you don’t let me win, then let’s break up.

148
00:15:28,348 --> 00:15:29,739
Oh...

149
00:15:29,739 --> 00:15:30,653
I lost.

150
00:15:30,653 --> 00:15:32,141
Not like this. Get up.

151
00:15:32,141 --> 00:15:33,537
(Laughing)

152
00:15:33,835 --> 00:15:34,756
Ouch!

153
00:15:34,756 --> 00:15:36,565
- You won.
- Hey.

154
00:15:36,956 --> 00:15:39,818
There you are. Why didn’t you pick up my call?

155
00:15:41,289 --> 00:15:43,404
Why didn’t you pick up my call last night?

156
00:15:45,285 --> 00:15:47,001
Are you working today?

157
00:15:47,299 --> 00:15:49,127
I thought you’d take a day off.

158
00:15:49,127 --> 00:15:51,596
Hewwww

159
00:15:51,950 --> 00:15:54,002
I’m not sick. Why should I take a day off?

160
00:15:54,002 --> 00:15:57,922
Well, I thought you’d go on a honeymoon...

161
00:15:57,922 --> 00:15:59,850
since last night...

162
00:16:00,260 --> 00:16:02,256
you slept at Phaya’s place, didn’t you?

163
00:16:02,591 --> 00:16:04,896
Hey!

164
00:16:04,896 --> 00:16:06,247
That’s right.

165
00:16:06,247 --> 00:16:07,478
How did you know?

166
00:16:07,478 --> 00:16:11,699
I had dinner around your flat last night. I wanted to drop by your place to give you some snacks...

167
00:16:11,699 --> 00:16:13,266
but you didn’t pick up my call.

168
00:16:13,266 --> 00:16:15,738
I went to your room and rang the bell but no one answered it.

169
00:16:15,738 --> 00:16:17,416
So, I figured out you might not be home.

170
00:16:17,603 --> 00:16:19,715
And then I saw you two coming to work together.

171
00:16:20,087 --> 00:16:21,047
It was so obvious.

172
00:16:21,047 --> 00:16:22,145
Yeah.

173
00:16:23,616 --> 00:16:26,143
You’re also wearing an oversized shrit.

174
00:16:26,143 --> 00:16:28,021
It must be Phaya’s.

175
00:16:28,021 --> 00:16:30,095
Hooo

176
00:16:30,095 --> 00:16:33,785
It’s pretty obvious. Just admit it.

177
00:16:33,785 --> 00:16:37,478
Come on. Just say it.

178
00:16:38,111 --> 00:16:41,604
From what I’ve analysed,

179
00:16:41,604 --> 00:16:46,908
our suspect seems to be lying. He tries to avoid our gaze and is also stuttering.

180
00:16:46,908 --> 00:16:47,681
(Laughing)

181
00:16:47,681 --> 00:16:49,759
- Yeah, stuttering indeed.
- Ouch.

182
00:16:49,759 --> 00:16:51,238
- Stuttering, you said?
- Ouch.

183
00:16:51,238 --> 00:16:53,036
Stuttering my arse.

184
00:16:53,036 --> 00:16:56,016
Babe, help me. I was just making fun of him a bit.

185
00:16:56,016 --> 00:16:58,522
- Ouch!
- Ouch!

186
00:16:58,522 --> 00:17:00,271
That’s enough.

187
00:17:00,271 --> 00:17:02,856
Yes, he slept at my place.

188
00:17:02,856 --> 00:17:06,391
My grandma and my sister wanted to thank him and treat him for dinner.

189
00:17:06,391 --> 00:17:09,013
Thank him for what?

190
00:17:09,896 --> 00:17:12,421
For loving me...

191
00:17:12,421 --> 00:17:15,108
For every time that you hug me...

192
00:17:15,108 --> 00:17:17,248
- Hug you?
- Ouch.

193
00:17:17,248 --> 00:17:21,172
Babe, help me.

194
00:17:21,172 --> 00:17:22,098
Help!

195
00:17:22,098 --> 00:17:23,450
Give it to me.

196
00:17:23,450 --> 00:17:24,415
Here, let me help.

197
00:17:24,415 --> 00:17:31,650
- I’ll help you.
- Ouch.

198
00:17:31,967 --> 00:17:36,224
I’m glad to see you smile like that again.

199
00:17:37,304 --> 00:17:39,376
And to have someone by your side.

200
00:17:40,791 --> 00:17:41,685
Phaya.

201
00:17:41,685 --> 00:17:42,821
What?

202
00:17:43,379 --> 00:17:45,469
Take care of my bro for me.

203
00:17:47,908 --> 00:17:49,113
Me too.

204
00:17:50,006 --> 00:17:51,102
You too, what?

205
00:17:51,102 --> 00:17:53,272
Please take care of my body too.

206
00:17:53,272 --> 00:17:54,545
Your body? Okay.

207
00:17:54,545 --> 00:17:55,740
Come, Tongthai.

208
00:17:55,740 --> 00:17:58,005
- Your body?
- Ouch.

209
00:17:58,005 --> 00:17:59,393
- One more.
- Ouch.

210
00:17:59,393 --> 00:18:00,847
Make it two.

211
00:18:00,847 --> 00:18:01,925
- Two more?
- Okay.

212
00:18:01,925 --> 00:18:02,925
You got it.

213
00:18:03,428 --> 00:18:05,304
Ouch! Ouch!

214
00:18:05,956 --> 00:18:07,557
Hey, guys!

215
00:18:08,004 --> 00:18:09,209
Hey!

216
00:18:10,606 --> 00:18:12,547
Inspector has called for a meeting about Kao’s case.

217
00:18:12,856 --> 00:18:14,971
- Hey!
- Hey!

218
00:18:17,696 --> 00:18:22,064
This morning, the bank called to confirm they had detected a new transaction on Kao’s credit card.

219
00:18:22,064 --> 00:18:23,753
But the person who used it isn’t Kao.

220
00:18:23,753 --> 00:18:25,873
It’s a teenage boy who is around 20 years old.

221
00:18:25,873 --> 00:18:27,999
He told us he went there to find some fish.

222
00:18:27,999 --> 00:18:30,652
And found Kao’s wallet in the swamp.

223
00:18:30,652 --> 00:18:32,315
Where’s this swamp?

224
00:18:32,315 --> 00:18:34,762
6km away from where Kao got off the taxi.

225
00:18:34,762 --> 00:18:36,341
We’ve checked via the satelltie.

226
00:18:36,341 --> 00:18:39,201
It’s a deserted forest with no residences nearby.

227
00:18:39,201 --> 00:18:41,194
Just a forest and the swamp where the wallet was found.

228
00:18:41,194 --> 00:18:43,076
What was Kao doing there?

229
00:18:52,032 --> 00:18:55,830
Phaya, Tharn, and Yai. Go find more evidence at the swamp.

230
00:18:55,830 --> 00:18:58,089
Tongthai and Kem, go to Ning’s place.

231
00:18:58,089 --> 00:18:59,853
Make her talk more about Kao.

232
00:18:59,853 --> 00:19:04,774
Ask her if Kao has any sibling or relative that he can rely on.

233
00:19:04,774 --> 00:19:07,156
Someone he really trusts that he can stay with them.

234
00:19:07,733 --> 00:19:09,437
Yes, sir.

235
00:19:24,276 --> 00:19:25,301
Found anything?

236
00:19:25,301 --> 00:19:26,411
Not yet.

237
00:19:46,855 --> 00:19:49,338
We haven’t seen any residence in this area.

238
00:19:49,673 --> 00:19:52,172
Why would Kao come here?

239
00:19:52,414 --> 00:19:55,689
Or did he come here to meet that person he was talking to on the phone?

240
00:19:55,689 --> 00:20:00,879
The taxi driver also said that Kao asked to get off after he hung up.

241
00:20:01,959 --> 00:20:06,004
At a place like this? It’s probably not something good.

242
00:20:06,004 --> 00:20:08,327
Let’s split up and look around the swamp.

243
00:20:08,327 --> 00:20:09,445
We might get more evidence from there.

244
00:20:09,445 --> 00:20:10,448
Okay.

245
00:20:13,464 --> 00:20:16,934
I tried to interview those people but still didn’t get anything new.

246
00:20:34,473 --> 00:20:37,183
Phaya! Phaya!

247
00:20:38,468 --> 00:20:40,589
Tharn, what’s wrong?

248
00:20:41,781 --> 00:20:44,163
You’d better get out of here.

249
00:20:45,410 --> 00:20:46,586
Why?

250
00:20:48,150 --> 00:20:50,353
Don’t you remember what the Abbot has warned you?

251
00:20:50,670 --> 00:20:53,712
That you should stay away from the river.

252
00:20:57,622 --> 00:20:59,087
Go and wait outside.

253
00:20:59,385 --> 00:21:01,587
Yai and I will take care of it here.

254
00:21:01,587 --> 00:21:03,368
I don’t want anything to happen to you.

255
00:21:04,094 --> 00:21:06,996
I’ll be fine. You’re here with me.

256
00:21:07,499 --> 00:21:10,044
You’ve seen a lot of visions where I was supposed to be dead.

257
00:21:10,044 --> 00:21:11,301
But I’m still alive.

258
00:21:15,285 --> 00:21:17,470
I trust you that you’d be able to take care of me.

